OL,3,CDonaldson denies meeting alleged
OL,4,Cvictim to nip claims 'in the bud'
OL,6,FMs Walsh pointed out that Mr Hoy's
OL,7,Fevidence to the court was that an
OL,8,F"allegation" had been made.
OL,10,FDonaldson said: "The word allegation
OL,11,Fwas never mentioned to me. If it had
OL,12,Fbeen mentioned I would have
OL,13,Fimmediately asked what it was about."
OL,15,FMs Walsh said: "You knew fine rightly
OL,16,Fwhat it was about."
OL,18,FDonaldson responded: "That is not
OL,19,Ftrue."
