OL,3,CDonaldson denies meeting alleged
OL,4,Cvictim to nip claims 'in the bud'
OL,6,FDonaldson said: "I absolutely did not
OL,7,Fshut her down."
OL,9,FThe barrister referred to evidence
OL,10,Ffrom Mr Hoy, where he said B was asked
OL,11,Fdid she want to "take it further".
OL,13,FMs Walsh suggested this referred to
OL,14,Fthe police being called.
OL,16,FDonaldson said: "I do not recall that
OL,17,Fbeing said."
OL,19,FMs Walsh then moved on to allegations
OL,20,Fagainst Donaldson made by Complainant
OL,21,FA.
