OL,3,CDonaldson denies meeting alleged
OL,4,Cvictim to nip claims 'in the bud'
OL,6,FShe asked if sexual abuse of A had
OL,7,Fstarted when she was of primary school
OL,8,Fage.
OL,10,FDonaldson said: "That is absolutely
OL,11,Fnot the case."
OL,13,FThe barrister asked if alleged abuse
OL,14,Fbegan with "touching outside of
OL,15,Fclothing".
OL,17,FHe said: "No, no, no."
OL,19,FShe put it to him that he had put his
OL,20,Ftongue in A's mouth on a number of
OL,21,Foccasions.
OL,26,@rD@QOUsD@NO]vD@LOUwD@IO]yD@JOUyD@VO]
